                      WE HANDPICK ELECTRIC TRANSPORT TO SUIT OUR CUSTOMER’S RIDES.

                      We don’t stock brands. We stock bikes for riders. Before stocking a product EcoMove ensures it meets our standard for affordability, quality and serviceability and matches them to specific commutes, so you can be sure you’re riding a quality bike.

                      No matter your situation, you’ll discover a wide selection of diverse electric bikes and mopeds at EcoMove from top brands including NIU, Raleigh, Muto, Mate, Haibike and more.

                      E-bikes are more popular than ever with even more people investing in a set of electric wheels. If you’d like help with choosing your new e-bike, our team is at hand to help, both online and in-store.

                      FINANCE

                      ABOUT ECOMOVE

                      Since launching in Bristol in 2019, EcoMove’s mission has been to deliver Bristol residents a more eco-friendly and sustainable means of transport.

                      With our range of products, we are helping residents switch to electric transport and reduce their impact on the environment. Bristol is considered to be the greenest city in the UK, and we are proud to be residents of the city.

                      We not only work to minimise our own carbon footprint, but we also work with local businesses to help reduce the impact they have on the environment.

                      We strongly believe that in order to reduce CO2 emissions, we all have a role to play, and our role is to show people an affordable, sustainable and enjoyable alternative to carbon. At EcoMove we offer a wide range of Electric Bikes and Electric Mopeds.

                      Frequently Asked Questions

                      Can I pay in installments/finance?

                      Yes, you can! Pay easily with PayPal or through your employer’s Cycle to Work scheme and spread the cost over up to 36 months.

                      Can I test Ride the bicycle / Ebike?

                      Yes, you can! Meet our experts, ask questions and safely try any of our e-bikes by booking a test ride outside the shop. You can enjoy your ride up to 30 minutes exploring Bristol’s scenic hills and vibrant streets.

                      Do you provide electric bicycle insurance?

                      We do not, but we can point you towards our partners at Laka where you can get a discount if you mention us here at EcoMove or simply give the discount code ECOMOVE30

                      Do I need a driving licence to ride an ebike in the UK?

                      No, you don’t need a driving licence to ride an e-bike in the UK, as long as it meets the EAPC (Electrically Assisted Pedal Cycle) regulations.

                      How Long does Delivery Take?

                      For all our products, delivery times depend on stock availability. We aim to deliver within 14 days of purchase. For e-bikes, you can pick them up in-store the same day or enjoy next-day delivery through our partner, Diamond Logistics.

                      Can I Ride Away on the day of purchase?

                      Yes, if your e-bike is in stock and assembled, you can ride away on the same day. If not, we’ll ship it to you at a nominal cost.

                      What Servicing and after sales support does EcoMove provide?

                      Your first e-bike service is on us, as long as it’s claimed within the first 6 months. Our certified technicians are also available to handle any e-bike or scooter repairs and maintenance.

                      What are the Running costs?

                      E-bikes are very affordable to run and charging costs around 10–20p per full charge, giving you up to 50 miles of range in general. Maintenance is minimal compared to cars or motorbikes.

                      What makes us eco?

                      Please see our about us page for all the great reasons you should choose EcoMove and find out what puts the eco in EcoMove.
